The paper deals with problems related to planar embeddings of graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The complexity analysis and approximation algorithms used in the paper involve concepts from algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The characterization of biconnected planar multi-graphs and the testing algorithm involve graph theory (cs.GT). The NP-completeness results and complexity dichotomy suggest that the paper may also be relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC).
